{{Infobox person |name = Dan Grimaldi |birth_name = Daniel Grimaldi |birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1952|1|20}} |birth_place = [[Brooklyn, New York]], U.S. |occupation = Actor |years_active = 1979-present }} '''Daniel "Dan" Grimaldi''' (born January 20, 1952) is an [[United States|American]] actor and mathematics professor who is known for his roles as twins [[Philly Parisi|Philly]] and [[Patsy Parisi]] on the [[HBO]] [[television|TV]] series ''[[The Sopranos]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/section/movies|title=Movies|accessdate=4 January 2018|website=Nytimes.com}}</ref>
==Career== In addition to his role on ''The Sopranos'', he has also had some minor film credits, most notably as mother-fixated pyromaniac Donny Kohler in the 1980 slasher film ''[[Don't Go in the House]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/19651/dont-go-in-the-house|title=Don't Go in the House|author=Ian Jane|publisher=[[DVD Talk]]|accessdate=2011-04-03}}</ref> and some guest TV appearances, including several episodes on ''[[Law & Order]]'' as well as appearing in 2011 as Tommy Barrone Sr. in "Moonlighting"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2108696/|title=Moonlighting|date=2 December 2011|publisher=|accessdate=4 January 2018|website=IMDb.com}}</ref> the 9th episode of the 2nd season of the [[CBS]] show ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]''. He appeared as an executive in the 2000 film [[The Yards]] and Grimaldi also voices "Frank" for the bestselling [[computer game]] ''[[Mafia (video game)|Mafia]]''.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}
==Education== Grimaldi has a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[mathematics]] from [[Fordham University]], a [[master's degree]] in [[operations research]] from [[New York University]], and a [[Ph.D.]] in [[data processing]] from the [[City University of New York]], and teaches in the Department of Mathematics and Computer Science at [[Kingsborough Community College]] in Brooklyn, New York.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingsborough.edu/FacultyProfiles/Daniel.Grimaldi/Pages/default.aspx|title=Kingsborough Community College -|website=Kingsborough.edu|accessdate=4 January 2018}}</ref>
