'''Mary Lucas''' née Anderson (1882&ndash;1952) was an English composer. She studied in [[Dresden]] and at the [[Royal College of Music]] with [[Herbert Howells]] and [[R.O. Morris]]. She married entrepreneur and inventor Ralph Lucas in 1903 and her son Colin became a noted architect.<ref>{{cite book |title=Connell, Ward and Lucas: Modern movement architects in England|first=Dennis|last=Sharp|first2=Sally|last2=Rendel|year=2008|accessdate=5 January 2011|format=Digitized online by GoogleBooks|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2jklBJ2AHvEC&pg=PA16&lpg=PA16&dq=Mary+Anderson+Lucas+composer&source=bl&ots=fPf-b4UqMM&sig=6Gote-L6xAtWfMupkdLYx9gibIk&hl=en&ei=i0ElTb_YIMT68Ab42cGgAQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CBkQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=Mary%20Anderson%20Lucas%20composer&f=false}}</ref> She gave up composition for a few years after she married, but returned to produce a number of successful compositions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musicweb-international.com/classrev/2002/oct02/distaff.htm#ixzz1AE0Cy97U|title=THE DISTAFF SIDE: SOME BRITISH WOMEN COMPOSERS|accessdate=5 January 2011}}</ref> Her ''Sonata'' for clarinet was written for Pauline Juler in 1938.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Clarinet: Volume 11|publisher=International Clarinet Society, Idaho State University. Dept. of Music|year=1983}}</ref> Lucas' papers are partially housed at the British Library,<ref>[http://www.concertprogrammes.org.uk/html/search/verb/GetRecord/4930 The British Library, Music Collections, Programmes and handbills relating to Mary Anderson Lucas]</ref> while some manuscripts and other papers are held at the [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]].
==Works== Selected works include: *''Sonata'' for clarinet (1938) *''The Wind'' (Text: James Stephens) *''Sawdust'', ballet (1941) *''Variations on a Theme of [[Purcell]]'' for string orchestra *''Trio'' for clarinet, viola and piano *''Rhapsody'' for flute, cello and piano *''The Book of Thel'', masque for solo voices, chorus, chamber orchestra, and male and female narrators (1935)
